<subSubSection id="09FC65500123FFB51AD8FB7AFD1EFAC4" pageId="14" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="415936DB0123FFB51AD8FB7AFD1EFAC4" blockId="14.[148,978,1058,1345]" pageId="14">
<emphasis id="7392EAC90123FFB51AD8FB7AFEDDFA89" bold="true" box="[172,288,1271,1292]" pageId="14">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of this species honors Professor Arthur M. Shapiro (University of 
<collectingRegion id="8322F8390123FFB51B5CFA9FFE77FAA2" box="[296,394,1298,1319]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="14">California</collectingRegion>
, Davis) for his constant help during my graduate studies, and his dedication to South American biogeographic studies.
</paragraph>
